==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[disseminatus]], past participle of [[disseminare]], from prefix ''dis-'' "in all directions" + ''seminare'' "to plant or propagate", from ''semen, seminis'' "seed."

===Pronunciation===
IPA: dɪ'sɛm.ɪn.eɪt

===Verb===
{{en-verb|disseminat|ed}}
# {{transitive}} To [[sow]] or [[broadcast]] as seed
# {{transitive}} To [[scatter]] for [[growth]] and [[propagation]], like seed
# {{transitive}} To [[spread]] [[abroad]]
# {{transitive}} To [[diffuse]]; as, principles, ideas, opinions, and errors are disseminated when they are spread abroad for propagation.
# {{intransitive}} To become [[scattered]].
::  ''The myth is disseminated throughout the southwest.''

